canonical:
  title: 孫端權知舒州軍州事
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 牒奉處分昔李弼有言大丈夫生世須履鋒刃以取功名安可碌碌依階求仕是乃蓄志能壯謀身克成夕脫羔裘朝驅熊軾不慙往哲其在玆乎前件官族繼興公術傳武子能揚儁氣久練雄師常安仡仡之徒果就循循之誘今則委之郡政試以公才旣逢豹變之秋善守龍舒之境爲邦致理必見三年有成向國輸忠勉令百姓無患卽迎帝賞更峻官榮事須差權知舒州軍州事
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 孫端權知舒州軍州事
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 牒奉處分。昔李弼有言。大丈夫生世。須履鋒刃。以取功名。安可碌碌依階求仕。是乃蓄志能壯。謀身克成。夕脫羔裘。朝驅熊軾。不慙往哲。其在玆乎。前件官。族繼興公。術傳武子。能揚儁氣。久練雄師。常安仡仡之徒。果就循循之誘。今則委之郡政。試以公才。旣逢豹變之秋。善守龍舒之境。爲邦致理。必見三年有成。向國輸忠。勉令百姓無患。卽迎帝賞。更峻官榮。事須差權知舒州軍州事。
korean:
  title: 손 단 권지 서주군 주사
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: 처분을 받들어 통첩한다. 옛날 이필(李弼)의 말에 “대장부가 세상에 태어나 마땅히 칼날을 밟아서 공명을 취해야 할 것인데, 어찌 녹록하게 품계에 따라 벼슬을 구하리오.” 하였다. 이것은 곧 웅장하게 하여 큰 뜻을 쌓아 몸의 성공을 도모한 것이다. 갑자기 선비 옷을 벗고 무사가 되어 나갔으니 선철(先哲)들에게 부끄럽지 않는 것이 바로 여기에 있는 것이다. 전건(前件)의 손단은 가문으로는 흥공(興公)을 이었고, 병술로는 손무자(孫武子)를 전해 받아, 능히 준걸한 기운을 떨치고, 오래 웅대한 군사를 조련시켰다. 항상 용맹스러운 무리를 안집(安集)하니, 과연 순순(循循)한 교유(敎誘)에도 잘 나아갔다. 지금 와서는 군정(郡政)을 맡겨 공무의 재재를 시험받게 하니, 표변(豹變)할 만한 좋은 때를 만나 용서(龍舒)의 땅을 잘 지켰다. 고을을 잘 다스려 3년 만에 이룸을 성취하여 국가를 위해 충성을 다하고 백성들에게 근심을 없도록 힘썼다. 그리하여 즉시 임금의 상(賞)을 맞이하였고 다시 영화로운 벼슬로 높게 한다. 마땅히 그에게 서주군 주사를 권지(權知)하도록 한다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1090_010_0210&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Appointment of Sun Dan as Provisional Administrator of Shuzhou
  author: Choe Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A proclamation is hereby issued.

    In ancient times, Li Bi declared: "A man of true stature, born into this world, must tread the edge of the blade to seize renown. How could he cower in the shade of rank, merely climbing the bureaucratic ladder?" This speaks of one who gathers resolve to build great ambition, who charts his course to accomplish himself. To cast off the scholar's robe and ride forth as a warrior—this is no shame before the ancients, and it finds its truest expression here.

    This Sun Dan inherits the legacy of his illustrious clan, carries forward the military wisdom of Sun Wu. With extraordinary talent he has wielded his prowess, and through long years has disciplined his troops with vision. Those fierce and fearless warriors he has ever gathered, those obstinate hearts he has gently guided—all have followed his way. Now, entrusted with the governance of a province, his talents are put to the test. In this season of transformation, let him guard well the lands of Long-shu. Let him bring order to this domain, and in three years his accomplishments shall bear fruit. In service to his nation, let him show unwavering loyalty. Let the common people know no suffering under his care. Thus shall he earn the sovereign's favor and rise to even greater honor.

    Therefore it is decreed: Sun Dan shall assume the position of Provisional Administrator of Shuzhou Military Prefecture.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Li Bi (李弼): A celebrated ancient Chinese general and strategist, cited here as an authority on masculine ambition and meritorious action.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Long-shu (龍舒): The poetic name for Shuzhou, derived from legendary associations.'
  - key: ''
    value: The 'season of transformation' (豹變) alludes to the I Ching concept of sudden, auspicious change, suggesting Sun Dan's appointment comes at a fortuitous moment.
  - key: ''
    value: This document is a formal appointment decree, composed in the elevated style typical of high-ranking official pronouncements in the Tang-influenced East Asian bureaucratic tradition.
